<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="1" id="a22769ca-f713-58b2-ac3a-8f57aa0f790a" activityNameId="48c12cfe-4bbc-5162-8b98-5daeafb23878" parentActivityId="188a4fb2-5ce9-544c-bc96-d2b6ee9074fd" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">market for flax straw, dew-retted</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts at the gate of flax production cultivation farm, within the geography of Europe.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the supply of 'flax, straw, dew-retted', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">This is the market for ' flax straw, dew-retted ', in the geography of Europe.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">This dataset represents the transport of 1 kg of flax straw, dew-retted, from the production farm to the place it is later used. No losses are considered in this dataset.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">The product 'flax straw, dew-retted' is a fiber crop and it is an annual crop.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="e2e1f67d-3393-4182-86f6-1ada2f77c3e5">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">0111:Growing of cereals (except rice), leguminous crops and oil seeds</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0723d252-7e2a-11de-9820-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RER</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Data represent the situation in Europe.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology/>
      <timePeriod startDate="2011-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The time period is the same as the in transforming activity for the same reference product.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
    <flowData>
      <intermediateExchange id="5e21564c-7164-553f-afec-72f8282d9b4f" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="1.0" intermediateExchangeId="8639d6b4-0c66-4e2a-9278-f14414427818" productionVolumeAmount="691634493.0">
        <name xml:lang="en">flax straw, dew-retted</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The data refer to flax straw, dew-retted in Western europe (France, Belgium and the Netherlands), the 1st step to produce European Flax™ fibre. European Flax™ is a certification of origin and traceability owned by the Alliance for European Flax-Linen and Hemp (formerly known as CELC) which covers 100% of the fibres obtained from western European retted flax plants, and guarantees third party verified traceability downstream. The unit is 1kg of retted flax plant  in 2014-2028 through Flax cultivation, retting and harvesting. Cultivation is modelled after the average common technical itinerary in the 3 countries including crop rotation; absence of irrigation (flax fields are not irrigated in western Europe, barring exceptional circumstances); reasoned use of fertiliser and pesticide; and 100% dew retting. It is 100% specific of Western Europe and cannot be used to represent any other geography. The detailed technical itinerary is available from the Alliance.</comment>
        <property propertyId="f2283db2-62e4-467f-b9ac-c4f45be563b4" amount="0.4275" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon allocation</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="a301a838-7975-4d89-9e74-8eb77ad03cd1" amount="0.475" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="c74c3729-e577-4081-b572-a283d2561a75" amount="0.0" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">fossil carbon content on a dry matter basis</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="6393c14b-db78-445d-a47b-c0cb866a1b25" amount="0.475" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, non-fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">biogene carbon content on a dry matter basis</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="3a0af1d6-04c3-41c6-a3da-92c4f61e0eaa" amount="0.9" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">dry mass</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="38f94dd1-d5aa-41b8-b182-c0c42985d9dc" amount="0.4298335793980902" unitId="7b75baf0-cbee-45e6-bf66-af119da06553">
          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">This is a simulated value based on the price range most commonly observed, btw 0,35 and 0,80 €/k for the period 2014-2018. It is to be noted that there is no stock market for flax straw:  prices are set for each lot, by farmers and mills (private or cooperative mills), and there is a large variability according to crop and weather conditions, as well as fibre prices. Source of the data: Flax-Linen Economic Observatory of the Alliance for European Flax-Linen &amp; Hemp, based on data collected by French interbranch representing the majority of European fibre flax straw. The prices were converted to EUR based on the annual exchange rates published by the European Central Bank (https://sdw.ecb.europa.eu/quickview.do?SERIES_KEY=120.EXR.A.AUD.EUR.SP00.A, last accessed on 2023-06-01) and adjusted for inflation relative to 2005 using the producer price index (PPI) of the euro area, published by eurostat (https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/STS_INPP_A__custom_6416181/default/table?lang=en, last accessed on 2023-06-01).</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="a9358458-9724-4f03-b622-106eda248916" amount="0.1111111" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">water content</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">water content on a dry matter basis</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="6d9e1462-80e3-4f10-b3f4-71febd6f1168" amount="0.1" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">water in wet mass</name>
